def: To be very abundant or exuberant; to be more than sufficient;as, the country superabounds with corn.

In an indicative manner; in a way to show or signify.
Like or pertaining to the Amioidei.-- n.
To move sidewise, as a crab. [Jocular]. Southey.
Not condensing; discharging the steam from the cylinder at apressure nearly equal to or above that of the atmosphere and not intoa condenser.
An appliance for the destruction of insects, consisting of ashallow iron box, containing kerosene or coated with tar or othersticky substance, which may be mounted on wheels.

A fetid European species of elder (Sambucus Ebulus); dwarfelder; wallwort; elderwort; -- called also Daneweed, Dane's weed, andDane's-blood.
The part of a projecting stone or brick inserted in a wall.Gwilt.
